On the other hand, the offer to convert Banca Transilvania was accepted by 83% of the customers with loans in francs due to the second successive discounts: the balance was reduced by the amount of risk and management fees paid by the client, then an additional reduction of 22.5% was applied to the balance in lei.
Both offers reduce the rates of their own customers, compared to what they paid equivalent monthly in lei before conversion.
Thus, Banca Transilvania reduces the rate by 42.5% and Bancpost, by 33% in the first three years and, theoretically, by 18% in the following years.
Benefits
The main advantage of covresia in lei of loans in CHF is that the currency risk is eliminated, the consumer being protected from future increases of franc, and the credit will be repaid in the currency in which he collects his salary.
Another major advantage of both conversion offers is that there is no reassessment of the property, no additional guarantees are required and no other proof of income.
In practice, there will be no new financial and legal analysis of the credit, nor will there be any additional costs as in the case of refinancing.
Also, both banks offer a discount on the monthly rate, compared to how much customers paid before conversion, equivalent to lei.
Risks
The problem is that the rate in the first years consists more of interest, and the client repays very little of the principal.
The Bancpost offer with very low interest rates in the first three years seems advantageous to customers.
