According to Dr. Gaylord Lopez, the director of the Georgia Anti-Poison Center, cases of hand detergent ingestion in children under the age of 12 reported at anti-poison centres went from 3,266 in 2010 to 16,117 in 2014.
"Children have more frequent access to these products and unfortunately a percentage of them reach the emergency room," Lopez told CNN.
