Doctors monitored her overnight in a separate children's hospital to identify signs of brain damage, as the girl fell and hit her head due to alcohol, Ritchie said.
"It was scary," Ortoria Scott, Nhaijah's mother, told CNN.
It could have been fatal.
Lopez recommended that parents and teachers use non-alcoholic wet products or napkins and no longer leave hand detergent out of the reach of children.
In addition to alcohol poisoning, some detergents have been associated with deaths.
