The situation is a little different when the answers of men and women are analysed separately.
Thus, 28% of men are very satisfied, 39% satisfied, 17% suitable, 6% very unsatisfied and 8% slightly unsatisfied.
As far as women are concerned, 33% declared satisfied, 24% very satisfied, 8% very unsatisfied, 14% slightly unsatisfied and 19% chose the right cathogory.
When we look at the degree of satisfaction (positive), we will notice that men are more satisfied.
As far as the neutral state is concerned, we see a two percent difference.
"In the same way in the very unsatisfactory situation, the biggest difference being recorded at the slightly unsatisfied answer where we see a difference of 6 percent," the communication also said.
The study also showed that a quarter of Romans (26%) spend an hour or even less time together, 18% spend between five and eight hours together, and 45% spend between two and four hours.
The authors of the study also say that "Romans need some more adventure in their lives (24%), followed by affection (21%), money (21%), safety (20%), new (19%), sex (19%), respect 18%, confidence 17%, pleasure 17%, connection 17%, knowledge 16%, protection 14%, importance 14%, learning 12%, freedom 11%, self-knowledge 10% and control 7%".
